# Testing Strategy

Testing should match risk. Add the smallest useful test that would catch a real regression.

## Unit Tests

Use Vitest for composables, pure utilities and focused behavior. Unit tests should be fast and should not depend on broad UI setup unless Nuxt runtime behavior is required.

## Component Tests

Add component tests when component behavior is complex enough to regress independently from a full page flow.

## E2E Tests

{% if use_playwright -%}
Use Playwright for critical user flows, routing, accessibility-sensitive interactions and high-value regressions.
Install browsers with `{{ package_manager }} exec playwright install` before the first local E2E run.
{% else -%}
Playwright is disabled in this generated project. Enable it when critical user flows need browser-level coverage.
{% endif -%}

## Check Command

`{{ package_manager }} run check` runs lint, typecheck and unit tests. Run it before handing work off for review. E2E tests are separate because they require installed browser binaries.

## Test Planning

Each implementation task should state:

- Unit coverage
- E2E coverage
- Manual checks
- Known test gaps
